Subject: [PATCH] swift_build_support/targets.py: fix NDK toolchain path for
 non-Linux build hosts

AndroidPlatform.ndk_toolchain_path() constructed the NDK prebuilt-clang
directory path from StdlibDeploymentTarget.host_target().name — Swift's
own host-target identifier (e.g. "macosx-arm64" on Apple Silicon macOS),
not the NDK's prebuilt-directory host tag. On Linux the two happen to
coincide ("linux-x86_64" either way), which is presumably why this went
unnoticed, but on a macOS build host Swift's tag ("macosx-arm64") doesn't
exist as an NDK directory at all — the NDK's own convention is
"darwin-x86_64" regardless of host CPU architecture (a universal
x86_64+arm64 Mach-O despite the name; see SwiftPM's
SWBAndroidPlatform/AndroidSDK.swift hostTag(_:) for the authoritative
mapping this mirrors). This broke resolving --host-cc/--host-cxx and the
native Clang tools path outright when cross-compiling to Android from
macOS.

Map the build host's platform.system() to the NDK's own host-tag
convention directly instead of reusing Swift's host-target name.

This patch is a candidate for filing upstream.

Sentinel: NUCLEUS_SWIFT_SOURCE_ANDROID_NDK_TOOLCHAIN_PATH_HOST_TAG

diff --git a/utils/swift_build_support/swift_build_support/targets.py b/utils/swift_build_support/swift_build_support/targets.py
index c2ee75f6626..b29f59df3b6 100644
--- a/utils/swift_build_support/swift_build_support/targets.py
+++ b/utils/swift_build_support/swift_build_support/targets.py
@@ -178,8 +178,25 @@ class AndroidPlatform(Platform):
         return options

     def ndk_toolchain_path(self, args):
+        # NOTE: StdlibDeploymentTarget.host_target().name (e.g.
+        # "macosx-arm64") is Swift's own host-target identifier, not the
+        # NDK's prebuilt-directory host tag. On Linux the two happen to
+        # coincide ("linux-x86_64" either way), which is presumably why
+        # this went unnoticed, but on a macOS build host Swift's tag
+        # ("macosx-arm64") doesn't exist as an NDK directory at all — the
+        # NDK's own convention is "darwin-x86_64" regardless of host arch
+        # (a universal x86_64+arm64 binary despite the name; see
+        # SWBAndroidPlatform/AndroidSDK.swift's hostTag(_:) for the
+        # authoritative mapping this mirrors).
+        system = platform.system()
+        if system == 'Darwin':
+            ndk_host_tag = 'darwin-x86_64'
+        elif system == 'Windows':
+            ndk_host_tag = 'windows-x86_64'
+        else:
+            ndk_host_tag = 'linux-x86_64'
         return '%s/toolchains/llvm/prebuilt/%s' % (
-            args.android_ndk, StdlibDeploymentTarget.host_target().name)
+            args.android_ndk, ndk_host_tag)

     def swiftpm_config(self, args, output_dir, swift_toolchain, resource_path):
         config_file = '%s/swiftpm-android-%s.json' % (output_dir, args.android_arch)
